<br>
&quot;Well whats do you know about it Edyin&quot; you ask, let see i'm a lv 60 mage on Rallos i've played since 2 weeks after the begining and o yah i got the best mage gear (and some the best general caster on RZ).  <br>
<br>
Heres my tatics broudly (for most classes) one i camp CC for roots webs(see where i'm going) or somethin new from luclin fungas gland(instant ensnare 10 charges) with mala i can land root 80% time and snare 90%.  so bam if its a caster my epic pet is beating the ever liveing crap out them and i'm dd/anulling at need.  <br>
<br>
Since SoV melee have realy come into there own pvp wise if anything a primal melee scares me more than any caster.<br>
For melee the thing i do is theres a quest in ss that you can get neck item that has 5 charges of one the Rune type buffs that helps tons with mellee.    My general melee tatic is use my rune buff, dmg shield, lev, buff pet up.  Mala the melee right off root/snare if i can, dispell pet if need be and kite his silly melee arse useing strafe (makes u ghost alot i know its cheap) if he stops to fight pet or cast on it nuke if he chases u kite and so on.  Bards are probly the only exeption to this they use the pet poof bug then you just got blast for all your worth (normaly 1 vs 1 the bard runs) .<br>
<br>
I can tell you this 1 VS 1 mages can hold there own or win but in large scale battle we get our butts handed to us (if you not got a healer that is and they normaly heal melee first).  Also a petless mage is a running mage but you all know about our lack of real stuns/knockbacks/roots/snares/rune .  thats it any question feel free to log on RZ and give a tell to &quot;Edyin&quot;<br>
<br>
