<br>
First off, if you don't play on a PvP server, you probably have very little idea about your class in PvP.  You can't say &quot;if the wizard doesn't have good resists&quot;.  On a PvP server, even the dumb ones have good resists by level 50.  Resist items are highly sought after by everyone, until they have a complete set.  There is no such thing as a wizard with less than 120 MR/FR.  To stand a chance, you must be level 60 and have Mala, because the lesser versions of the spell simply will not stick on anyone ever.<br>
<br>
I've played a warrior and a magician.  As my warrior (level 58) , magicians were one of my favorite targets.  The ONLY way a magician had a chance against me was if they got the jump on me, had SOW, had SOW on the pet, I didn't have SOW and I was out of egg shaped pumice and golem rods.<br>
<br>
Under any other circumstance, I could beat the mage down no problem, indoors, outdoors, didn't matter.  They were dead long before their pet had me worrying.  If Tantor's Tusk couldn't fix them, switching to my one-handers and turning on Mighty Strike would.  If worse came to worse, I could always just get away from them.<br>
<br>
Mages lack:<br>
1) A method of escape, like shadowstep.<br>
2) A method of damage mitigation, like Rune.<br>
3) A 'resistless' attack spell, like Splurt or Lure<br>
4) A way to stop runners, like Snare<br>
<br>
Combine those together and you have a class that's going to have a real struggle in PvP.<br>
<br>
Add in the bugs that people can use to make your pet kill itself, and mages have serious issues.<br>
<br>
You can go on all day about how you killed someone with your mage, but remember the old gaming addage: &quot;Anything works against stupid people&quot;.  I don't doubt that you can beat a wizard on a non-PvP server.  He has very little experience.  On a PvP server, though, magicians are the bottomfeeders.  We simply don't have the spells to compete one on one.<br>
<br>
I've killed my fair share.  I was, at one point, the #1 ranked magician in points on Sullon Zek (before I went to DAOC for a while).  Virtually all of my solo kills came from me getting the jump on someone at a bad time (for them).<br>
<br>
Mages are like backstabbers.  Can't go toe to toe with someone.  The only way we can work over someone is to hit them from behind.  If PvP were drag racing, mages would always need a 1 second head start just to stand a chance of pulling up even at the finish line.<br>
